sentences: Elkan Bauer was an Austrian composer and friend and contemporary of Johann Strauss II born in Nikolsburg, on April 4, 1852.
After being taken prisoner by the Germans in 1942, the Nazis burned all his possessions including his house, his documents and his scores.
He was killed in the concentration camp of Theresienstadt at the age of ninety, on September 20, 1942.
The writer Elisa Springer, his maternal granddaughter, who wrote a book, Das Schweigen der Lebenden (The Silence of the Living), preserved these scores.
